In article <16FBFFC84S86.C445585@mizzou1.missouri.edu>,
 <C445585@mizzou1.missouri.edu> wrote:
> 
>   What is a "2-adic" number?  The description Bruce Schneier gave of
>one of the papers from Eurocrypt 94 made it sound like an unsigned binary
>integer.  Can anyone fill me in?

Basically, yes.  But it's infinite to the left, and in some formulations
may have a finite number of bits to the right of the decimal point.

See Knuth, Volume 2, exercise 31 (this is the second edition; I
don't know if the same exercise is in the first) for an introduction.
